    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 6.72,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.72,
      "end": 14.24,
      "text": "information and to find out how to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org. Recording by Marion",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 14.24,
      "end": 23.96,
      "text": "Brown, Toronto, Canada. ASOP's Fables. Venus and the Cat. A cat fell in love with a handsome",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 23.96,
      "end": 29.82,
      "text": "young man and begged the goddess Venus to change her into a woman. Venus was very gracious",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 29.82,
      "end": 35.28,
      "text": "about it and changed her at once into a beautiful maiden, whom the young man fell in love with",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 35.28,
      "end": 41.04,
      "text": "at first sight and shortly afterwards married. One day Venus thought she would like to see",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 41.04,
      "end": 46.5,
      "text": "whether the cat had changed her habits as well as her form, so she let a mouse run loose",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 46.5,
      "end": 51.72,
      "text": "in the room where they were. Forgetting everything, the young woman had no sooner seen the mouse",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 51.72,
      "end": 57.96,
      "text": "than up she jumped and was after it like a shot at which the goddess was so disgusted that she",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 57.96,
      "end": 63.72,
      "text": "changed her back again into a cat. End of Venus and the Cat.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
